 <h1>How to use Show Close Tab button?</h1>
 <p>1. Click <strong>the extension button</strong> to display the settings screen.</p>
  <div class="image-container">
    <img src="images/screenshot1.png" alt="show settings screen screenshot">
  </div>
  <p>2. After clicking <strong>the drop-down menu</strong> and selecting the button you need, press <strong>the + button</strong> on the right to add a new button.</p>
  <div class="image-container">
    <img src="images/screenshot2.png" alt="show settings screen screenshot">
  </div>
    <p>3. After adding a button, you can select the position of the button on the web page and the horizontal or vertical arrangement of the button, and then click <strong>the Apply button</strong> to complete the settings.</p>
  <div class="image-container">
    <img src="images/screenshot3.png" alt="show settings screen screenshot">
  </div>
    <p>4. All buttons are displayed on the web page</p>
  <div class="image-container">
    <img src="images/screenshot4.png" alt="show settings screen screenshot">
  </div>
    <p>5. Supplement: In Firefox under Windows, you can change the position of the button by <strong>dragging</strong> it.</p>
  <div class="image-container">
    <img src="images/screenshot5.png" alt="drap the button screenshot">
  </div>
  
